# Template notes

This project was scaffolded from the kaliki-template stack. This file documents
the wiring conventions so you can extend it cleanly.

## Adding a domain (the "enumeration points")

A domain touches a fixed set of places. To add `widgets`:

1. `api/services/widgets.yaml` тАФ define the contract first.
2. `backend/internal/widgets/{service,store}.go` тАФ handler + data access.
3. `backend/sql/schema/00NN_widgets.sql` тАФ goose-style migration.
4. `backend/internal/server/server.go` тАФ register routes:
   `widgets.New(db).Register(api)`.
{%- if include_frontend %}
5. `frontend/` тАФ regenerate the API client, then build the screen.
{%- endif %}

The `items` domain is a complete worked example of all of the above.

