## Admin / secondary API surface split (upgrade path)

This project ships a **single** generated API client. Admin-only endpoints are
expected to be protected by **server-side authz** тАФ that is the real security
boundary.

When you want to additionally keep admin endpoints out of the customer app's
client bundle and docs, adopt the split-spec pattern:

1. Tag operations in `api/services/*.yaml` with `x-audience: public | admin`.
2. Build **two** combined specs (public, admin) from the redocly config.
3. Generate **two** Dart clients; the customer app imports only the public one,
   the admin app imports both.

This is documentation-only here тАФ wire it when the admin app needs it. Note it
hides endpoints from the bundle, it is **not** a substitute for authz.

## Tier-2 modules

These are wired as integration points (client init + config), not full business
logic тАФ extend them for your product:

{% if caching == 'redis' %}- `internal/cache` тАФ Redis client (request-time caching).
{% endif %}{% if eventing == 'kafka-redpanda' %}- `internal/events` тАФ Kafka/Redpanda publisher. Use the `outbox` table for
  transactional, at-least-once delivery (write events in the same tx as the
  domain change, then relay rows where `published_at IS NULL`).
{% endif %}{% if payments == 'razorpay' %}- `internal/payments` тАФ Razorpay client. Add orders/webhooks/subscriptions.
{% endif %}{% if push_notifications == 'firebase' %}- `internal/push` тАФ Firebase Cloud Messaging. Set `firebase.credentials_file`.
{% endif %}{% if object_storage == 's3' %}- `internal/storage` тАФ S3-compatible object store. Use `PresignPut`/presigned
  URLs; follow ownership prefixes (`users/<id>/...`, etc.).
{% endif %}Each is constructed in `internal/server/server.go`; inject it into the domains
that need it.

## Testing

Integration-style handler tests register real routes on a real gin router and
hit real endpoint paths, verifying DB state (not just HTTP status). They run
against a throwaway postgres.

```sh
# start the test database
docker compose -f backend/docker/docker-compose-test.yaml up -d

# run tests (-p 1 serializes packages; they share one test DB)
cd backend && TEST_DATABASE_URL="postgres://test_user:test_password@localhost:25432/test_db?sslmode=disable" \
  go test -p 1 ./...
# or: make test
```

Conventions: one top-level `Test<OperationId>` per OpenAPI operation; subtests
in the order `success`, `authorization`, `validation`, `not_found`, `conflict`.
Shared helpers live in `internal/testsupport`. See `internal/items` and
`internal/auth` for worked examples.

